!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

illegal /ɪˈliːɡəl/

(illegals) 

1. ADJ If something is illegal , the law says that it is not allowed. 非法的 

例： It is illegal to intercept radio messages. 窃听无线电信息是违法的。 

例： ...illegal drugs. …非法毒品。 

2. illegally ADV 非法地 [ADV with v] 

例： He was convicted of illegally using a handgun. 他被判非法使用手枪。 

3. ADJ Illegal immigrants or workers have travelled into a country or are working without official permission. (移民) 非法入境的; (工人) 非法务工的 [ADJ n] 

4. N-COUNT Illegal immigrants or workers are sometimes referred to as illegals . 非法移民; 非法劳工 

例： ...a clothing factory where many other illegals also worked. …一家允许很多其他非法劳工工作的服装厂。

</div>

